Key Match Events: Ireland defeats Pakistan by 5 wickets in historic T-20 win at Clontarf Cricket Club
Craig Young's two crucial wickets in one over of Babar Azam and Azam Khan put the Pakistan middle order under tremendous pressure
Andrew Balbirnie's counter-attacking innings (77 off 55 balls) led to victory
Miscellaneous Highlights: The loss to Ireland puts Pakistan 1-0 down in the three-match T20 series
The two teams will also face each other in the group stages of the T20 World Cup next month
Others: Saim Ayub (45 off 29 balls) and skipper Babar Azam (57 off 43 balls) were the top scorers for Pakistan
Curtis Campher took a leg bye off the penultimate ball of the match to seal a memorable victory for his side
